    {
      "para_id": "Q004103.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) When I , Lipit-Eštar , the humble shepherd of Nibru , the true farmer of Urim , ceaseless provider of Eridug , the en priest suitable for Unug , king of Isin , king of Sumer and Akkad , the favourite of Inana , established justice in Sumer and Akkad , then for Nanaya , the beloved child of Inana , my lady , I built the E-me-urur , her beloved storehouse in Isin ."
    }
  ],
